  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the broccoli in half lengthways, then into roughly 2cm pieces. Finely chop the chilli and garlic and set them aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place a deep-sided pan over a medium heat, add a generous drizzle of olive oil and then de-case your sausages and crumble the meat straight into the pan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "After a few minutes, once the sausages have some colour, add the garlic and chilli and fry for another 2 mins, then add the broccoli and a big pinch of salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Give it a good stir and pour in the wine to deglaze. Make sure you give the bottom of the pan a good scrape with your spoon."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, put the pasta on to boil in plenty of salted water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Let the wine bubble away until it’s reduced by three-quarters, then turn off the heat. Once the pasta is al dente, spoon it into the broccoli pan along with half a mug of the pasta cooking water. Set over a medium heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take your time here and stir the pasta as everything bubbles – you want the water to reduce a bit and the whole thing to become saucy and creamy. Squeeze in the lemon, finely chop and add the parsley and half the cheese."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Stir again, plate up and finish with more cheese and black pepper."
    }
  ],
